b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](av187.htm)  [Next](av189.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n## VI, 26. Charm to avert evil.\n\n1\\. Let me go, O evil; being powerful, take thou pity on us! Set me, O evil,\nunharmed, into the world of happiness!  \n2\\. If, O evil, thou dost not abandon us, then do we abandon thee at the fork\nof the road. May evil follow after another (man)!  \n3\\. Away from us may thousand-eyed, immortal (evil) dwell! Him whom we hate\nmay it strike, and him whom we hate do thou surely smite!\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: VI, 114. Expiatory formula for imperfections in the\nsacrifice](av189.htm)\n\n'